  "text": "The Kafka consumer fetch request to ConsumerRecords processing chain follows this flow:\n\n1. ENTRY POINT - KafkaConsumer.poll(Duration timeout) delegates to ClassicKafkaConsumer.poll(Duration timeout) (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/KafkaConsumer.java, clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/ClassicKafkaConsumer.java:894).\n\n2. REQUEST SENDING PHASE:\n   - ClassicKafkaConsumer.poll() calls ClassicKafkaConsumer.pollForFetches(Timer) (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/ClassicKafkaConsumer.java:690) which orchestrates fetching.\n   - pollForFetches() invokes Fetcher.sendFetches() (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/Fetcher.java:105) to send fetch requests.\n   - Fetcher.sendFetches() calls Fetcher.sendFetchesInternal() (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/Fetcher.java:184) which iterates over nodes and sends requests.\n\n3. REQUEST BUILDING PHASE:\n   - Fetcher.sendFetchesInternal() calls AbstractFetch.prepareFetchRequests() (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/AbstractFetch.java:412) to prepare fetch requests for all fetchable partitions organized by node.\n   - prepareFetchRequests() builds a FetchSessionHandler.Builder for each node and creates FetchRequest.PartitionData for each partition.\n   - For each node, AbstractFetch.createFetchRequest(Node, FetchSessionHandler.FetchRequestData) (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/AbstractFetch.java:301) constructs a FetchRequest.Builder using FetchRequest.Builder.forConsumer() (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/common/requests/FetchRequest.java:166).\n   - The builder configures isolation level, max bytes, metadata, and removed/replaced partitions before being sent via client.send().\n\n4. NETWORK TRANSMISSION:\n   - Fetcher.sendFetchesInternal() sends the built FetchRequest.Builder to the network client and registers response listeners.\n   - For asynchronous handling, FetchRequestManager follows a similar pattern via FetchRequestManager.poll() and FetchRequestManager.pollInternal() (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/FetchRequestManager.java:103, 137).\n\n5. RESPONSE PARSING PHASE:\n   - Upon receiving the response, AbstractFetch.handleFetchSuccess(Node, FetchSessionHandler.FetchRequestData, ClientResponse) (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/AbstractFetch.java:150) is invoked.\n   - handleFetchSuccess() extracts the FetchResponse from the ClientResponse and calls FetchResponse.responseData(Map<Uuid, String>, short) (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/common/requests/FetchResponse.java:98) to parse partition data and topic IDs.\n   - For each partition, a CompletedFetch is created with the FetchResponseData.PartitionData and added to the FetchBuffer.\n\n6. RECORD EXTRACTION AND DESERIALIZATION:\n   - ClassicKafkaConsumer.pollForFetches() calls Fetcher.collectFetch() (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/Fetcher.java:145) which delegates to FetchCollector.collectFetch(FetchBuffer) (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/FetchCollector.java:92).\n   - FetchCollector.collectFetch() iterates through completed fetches and calls FetchCollector.fetchRecords(CompletedFetch, int) (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/FetchCollector.java:150) for each partition.\n   - FetchCollector.fetchRecords() calls CompletedFetch.fetchRecords(FetchConfig, Deserializers, int) (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/CompletedFetch.java:252) to extract and deserialize records from record batches.\n   - CompletedFetch.fetchRecords() iterates through batches, calls CompletedFetch.parseRecord(Deserializers, TopicPartition, Optional<Integer>, TimestampType, Record) (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/CompletedFetch.java:307) for each record to deserialize key/value and create ConsumerRecord objects.\n\n7. FETCH AGGREGATION:\n   - FetchCollector.fetchRecords() wraps the extracted records in a Fetch object via Fetch.forPartition(TopicPartition, List<ConsumerRecord>, boolean, OffsetAndMetadata) (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/Fetch.java:43).\n   - Multiple Fetch objects from different partitions are aggregated together.\n\n8. FINAL CONSUMERRECORDS CONSTRUCTION:\n   - ClassicKafkaConsumer.poll() constructs ConsumerRecords<K, V> (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/ConsumerRecords.java) passing the aggregated records and next offsets metadata.\n   - The ConsumerRecords object is returned to the user with records organized by TopicPartition.\n\nKEY SESSION MANAGEMENT: FetchSessionHandler (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/FetchSessionHandler.java) manages fetch sessions to optimize requests by tracking which partitions are already known to the broker, reducing request size and improving efficiency."
